--------

I personally think the above answer isn't very helpful. I took CS 160 and thought it was amazingly useful; no one will buy or use software that they can't figure out how to use. It teaches a completely different side of CS and in my opinion it should be a required course. If you have zero-interest in front-end systems or human computer interaction, it may not be the best class to take, but beyond that it is 100% a great class to take. I can't speak to how the particular workload you mentioned is, but 160 itself varies. I thought the workload was pretty light and very manageable, but it does vary from semester to semester. 

tldr; yes, it's very useful and you should take it.

children.subject:
All four together would be a difficult schedule. 61c especially has a lot of projects and EE homework’s are fairly time consuming. I wouldn’t take all four, unless you really think you can handle the workload. It’s going to be a lot of work if you do. 

I’d pick the three that give the best schedule of homework and exams, or the three you most want to keep. Or, if you think you won’t be able to get into one of the classes easily in the future, keep that one.
